    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Animals characterized by a varied diet of both plant and animal materials, as distinguished from a meat-eating carnivore or a plant-eating herbivore. Bears are examples of omnivores.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
